07/04/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- US Ambassador to Tirana John Withers asked on Sunday (April 6th) that Chief Prosecutor Ina Rama investigate and sentence all those responsible for last month's munitions explosions at a weapons depot in the village of Gerdec.
A total of 27 people were killed in the blast and more than 300 were injured.
Withers said all parties involved should face justice, no matter what their rank or standing.
He added that six FBI agents are helping with the investigation.
(TopChannel, Koha Jone, AP - 06/04/08)
